entry.database_comments: General Comments: Pattern can be indexed with monoclinic cell: a=24.145, b=11.577, c=19.990, β=111.28. Pattern submitted by the Japanese Committee on Powder Diffraction Data, Tokyo, Japan. The present phase has a structure based on a pseudo-FCC subcell with an approximate lattice constant of 5.4 and melts congruently at 950 C. Melting Point: 1223 K. Sample Preparation: The sample was prepared by solid-state reaction. The starting materials ''Bi2 O3'' and ''V2 O5'' were thoroughly mixed in the proportion of ''Bi2 O3'':''V2 O5'' molar ratio of 23:4. The mixture was transferred into a covered platinum crucible and heated around 850 C for 50 hours. The sample was then air quenched and ground well in an agate mortar. In order to complete the reaction, the same heat treatment was repeated. Warning: Lines with abs(delta 2Theta)>0.06 DEG.
